Additionally, the paper discusses algorithmic challenges and opportunities for future work, which are relevant to the cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.CG (computational geometry) sub-categories. The paper also mentions recent progress in theory and practice, which suggests that it may be relevant to the cs.DM (discrete mathematics) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses applications of sparse polynomials in control systems, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the cs.SY (systems and control) sub-category.
